very migrated row. In the legacy model, users could upload multiple docs under the same category/type. After this migration, multiple rows can remain `is_current=true` for a single `(trailer, document_type)`. The UI grouping logic (`assets.tsx`) keeps only one `current` per type and only shows rows with `isCurrent=false` in history, so additional legacy rows become effectively invisible (not current, not history) depending on iteration overwrite. This violates preservation/visibility and version-history expectations.

2) **No hard guard to enforce a single current row per type** (high impact): schema adds only a non-unique index (`idxCurrent`) rather than a unique partial constraint for `(trailer_id, document_type) WHERE is_current AND deleted_at IS NULL`. Concurrency or bad legacy state can create multiple currents and inconsistent behavior.

